#2 Logistic_ Regression using one__variable

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load the_dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Cancer_dataset1.csv")
df = df.assign(
    mean_area=df["mean_area"].fillna(df["mean_area"].mean()),
    outcome=df["outcome"].fillna(df["outcome"].mode()[0])
)

# Prepare_featre & target variable
X = df["mean_area"].values.reshape(-1, 1)  # Feature
y = np.where(df["outcome"] == "N", 0, 1)   # Convert_to_numeric__(N=0, R=1)

# Scatter_plot of_dataset
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.scatter(df["mean_area"], y, c=y, cmap="bwr", alpha=0.6, edgecolors="k")
plt.xlabel("Mean_Area (Breast_Cancer_Feature)")
plt.ylabel("Recurrence (0 = No, 1 = Yes)")
plt.title("Scatter Plot Mean_Area vs. Cancer_Recurrence")
plt.show()

# Normalize_featre for better convergence
X_mean_, X_std_ = X.mean(), X.std()
X_norm_ = (X - X_mean_) / X_std_

# Manual train-test split (80% train, 20% test)
np.random.seed(42)
indies__ = np.random.permutation(len(X_norm_))
splt_id_x = int(0.8 * len(X_norm_))
trn_id_x, tst_id_x = indies__[:splt_id_x], indies__[splt_id_x:]
X_trn_, X_tst_ = X_norm_[trn_id_x], X_norm_[tst_id_x]
y_trn, y_tst_ = y[trn_id_x], y[tst_id_x]

# Sigmoid function
def sigmoid(z):
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))

# Logistic Regression function using Gradient Descent
def logistic_regression(X, y, lr=0.01, epochs=5000):
    m, n = X.shape
    X_bis = np.c_[np.ones((m, 1)), X]  # Add bias term (intercept)
    theta__ = np.zeros(n + 1)  # Initialize model parameters
    
    loss_histry_ = []
    
    for _ in range(epochs):
        z = np.dot(X_bis, theta__)
        h = sigmoid(z)
        gradient = np.dot(X_bis.T, (h - y)) / m  # Compute gradients
        theta__ -= lr * gradient  # Update parameters
        loss = -np.mean(y * np.log(h) + (1 - y) * np.log(1 - h))  # Compute loss
        loss_histry_.append(loss)

    return theta__, loss_histry_

# Train the model
theta__, loss_histry_ = logistic_regression(X_trn_.reshape(-1, 1), y_trn, lr=0.01, epochs=5000)

# Plot loss curve
plt.plot(loss_histry_)
plt.xlabel("Iterations")
plt.ylabel("Loss")
plt.title("Logistic_Regression_Loss")
plt.show()

# Make Predictions on Test__Data
X_tst_bis = np.c_[np.ones((X_tst_.shape[0], 1)), X_tst_]  # Add bias_term
y_prd_prob__ = sigmoid(np.dot(X_tst_bis, theta__))
y_prd_ = (y_prd_prob__ >= 0.5).astype(int)

# Compute Confusion__Matrix
TP = np.sum((y_prd_ == 1) & (y_tst_ == 1))  # True Positives
TN = np.sum((y_prd_ == 0) & (y_tst_ == 0))  # True Negatives
FP = np.sum((y_prd_ == 1) & (y_tst_ == 0))  # False Positives
FN = np.sum((y_prd_ == 0) & (y_tst_ == 1))  # False Negatives

conf_matix = np.array([[TN, FP], [FN, TP]])

# Calculate performance metrics manually
accuacy = (TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN)
preision = TP / (TP + FP) if (TP + FP) != 0 else 0
recll = TP / (TP + FN) if (TP + FN) != 0 else 0
f1_score__ = 2 * (preision * recll) / (preision + recll) if (preision + recll) != 0 else 0

# Print Performance Metrics
print(f"Accuracy: {accuacy:.4f}")
print(f"Precision: {preision:.4f}")
print(f"Recall: {recll:.4f}")
print(f"F1 Score: {f1_score__:.4f}")

# Print Confusion_Matrix with Labls
print("\nConfusion Matrix:")
print(f"                Predicted No   Predicted Yes")
print(f"Actual No     |    {TN}         {FP}  |  (TN  FP)")
print(f"Actual Yes    |    {FN}         {TP}  |  (FN  TP)")

# Plot Confusion Matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))
sns.heatmap(conf_matix, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues", 
            xticklabels=["No_Recurrence", "Recurrence_"], 
            yticklabels=["No_Recurrence", "Recurrence_"])
plt.xlabel("Predicted_Label")
plt.ylabel("True_Label")
plt.title("Confusion_Matrix for Logistic_Regression (mean_area)")
plt.show()

# Print Final Theta__ Values
print("Final Model Parameters (Theta__):", theta__)

# Convert metrics to percentages
accracy_per = accuacy * 100
precion_per = preision * 100
recll_per = recll * 100
f1_score_per = f1_score__ * 100

# Print Performance Metrics as Percentages
print(f"Accuracy using one varaible: {accracy_per:.2f}%")
print(f"Precision using one varaible: {precion_per:.2f}%")
print(f"Recall using one varaible: {recll_per:.2f}%")
print(f"F1 Score using one varaible: {f1_score_per:.2f}%")

##3a Logistic_Regression using Multiple_Varaibl
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Cancer_dataset1.csv")

# Selcted_Featres
selcted_featres = [
    "mean_radius", "mean_texture", "mean_perimeter", "mean_area", 
    "mean_smoothness", "mean_compactness", "mean_concavity", "mean_concave_points", 
    "mean_fractal_dimension", "se_perimeter", "se_texture", "se_area"
]

# Fill_missing_vals using_mean, only nume_colns
df_cln = df.copy()
df_cln[selcted_featres] = df[selcted_featres].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')  # Ensure numeric conversion
df_cln[selcted_featres] = df_cln[selcted_featres].fillna(df_cln[selcted_featres].mean())

# Compute_coreltion_matx
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
corelation_matx = df[selcted_featres].corr()
# Plot_heatmap
sns.heatmap(corelation_matx, annot=True, fmt=".2f", cmap="coolwarm", linewidths=0.5, center=0, vmin=-1, vmax=1)
# Adding__Title
plt.title("Feature_Correlation Heat_map")
# Create separate_figure for the color interpretation legend
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 1))  # Adjust width for better spacing
ax.set_axis_off()  # Hide axis
# Define color legend patches with_corrected white patch
legd_labls = [
    Patch(facecolor="darkred", label="Strong Positive Correlation (r  1.0)"),
    Patch(facecolor="lightcoral", label="Moderate Positive Correlation (r  0.5 to 0.9)"),
    Patch(facecolor="white", edgecolor="black", label="No Correlation (r  0)"),  # Fixed here
    Patch(facecolor="lightblue", label="Moderate Negative Correlation (r  -0.5 to -0.9)"),
    Patch(facecolor="darkblue", label="Strong Negative Correlation (r  -1.0)"),
]
# Add legend below the heatmap
legend = ax.legend(handles=legd_labls, loc="center", ncol=5, frameon=False)
plt.show()

# Extract features (X) and target variable (y)
X = df_cln[selcted_featres].values
y = np.where(df_cln["outcome"] == "N", 0, 1)  # Convert "N" to 0, "R" to 1
# Normalize features
X_mean_, X_std = X.mean(axis=0), X.std(axis=0)
X_norm = (X - X_mean_) / X_std
# Split into training and testing sets manually
trn_sze = int(0.8 * X_norm.shape[0])
X_trn, X_test = X_norm[:trn_sze], X_norm[trn_sze:]
y_trn, y_tst = y[:trn_sze], y[trn_sze:]

# Sigmoid function
def sigmoid(z):
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))
# Logistic Regression model
def logistic_regression(X, y, alpha=0.01, iterations=1000):
    m, n = X.shape
    X_bias = np.c_[np.ones((m, 1)), X]  # Add bias term
    theta = np.zeros(n + 1)  # Initialize parameters
    loss_history = []

    for _ in range(iterations):
        z = np.dot(X_bias, theta)
        h = sigmoid(z)
        loss = -np.mean(y * np.log(h) + (1 - y) * np.log(1 - h))
        gradient = np.dot(X_bias.T, (h - y)) / m
        theta -= alpha * gradient
        loss_history.append(loss)
    
    return theta, loss_history

# Train the model
the_ta_ful, loss_history_full = logistic_regression(X_trn, y_trn)

# Make Predictions
def predict(X, theta):
    X_bias = np.c_[np.ones((X.shape[0], 1)), X]
    return (sigmoid(np.dot(X_bias, theta)) >= 0.5).astype(int)

y_pred_full = predict(X_test, the_ta_ful)

# Compute Confusion Matrix
TP = np.sum((y_pred_full == 1) & (y_tst == 1))
TN = np.sum((y_pred_full == 0) & (y_tst == 0))
FP = np.sum((y_pred_full == 1) & (y_tst == 0))
FN = np.sum((y_pred_full == 0) & (y_tst == 1))

conf_matrix_full = np.array([[TN, FP], [FN, TP]])

# Print Confusion Matrix
print("\nConfusion Matrix (Full Model):")
print(f"                Predicted No   Predicted Yes")
print(f"Actual No     |    {TN}         {FP}  |  (TN  FP)")
print(f"Actual Yes    |    {FN}         {TP}  |  (FN  TP)")

# Calculate Performance Metrics
accuracy_full = (TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN) * 100
precision_full = (TP / (TP + FP) * 100) if (TP + FP) != 0 else 0
recall_full = (TP / (TP + FN) * 100) if (TP + FN) != 0 else 0
f1_score_full = (2 * (precision_full * recall_full) / (precision_full + recall_full)) if (precision_full + recall_full) != 0 else 0

# Print Performance Metrics
print(f"Accuracy: {accuracy_full:.2f}%")
print(f"Precision: {precision_full:.2f}%")
print(f"Recall: {recall_full:.2f}%")
print(f"F1 Score: {f1_score_full:.2f}%")

# Plot Confusion Matrix as Heatmap
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 5))
sns.heatmap(conf_matrix_full, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues", xticklabels=["Predicted No", "Predicted Yes"], yticklabels=["Actual No", "Actual Yes"])
plt.title("Confusion Matrix (Full Model)")
plt.ylabel("Actual")
plt.xlabel("Predicted")
plt.show()

# Plot Performance Metrics
metris_ful = [accuracy_full, precision_full, recall_full, f1_score_full]
metris_nams = ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1 Score']

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
plt.bar(metris_nams, metris_ful, color=['blue', 'green', 'orange', 'red'])
plt.ylim(0, 100)
plt.title("Model Performance Metrics (Full Model)")
plt.ylabel("Percentage")
plt.show()

# Plot Training Loss Curve
plt.plot(loss_history_full)
plt.xlabel("Iterations")
plt.ylabel("Loss")
plt.title("Training Loss Curve (Full Model)")
plt.show()

# Print Final Model Parameters
print("Final Model Parameters (Theta for 12 Features):", the_ta_ful)

#3b Forward selection_
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Cancer_dataset1.csv")

# Selected__Features
seleted_featues = [
    "mean_radius", "mean_texture", "mean_perimeter", "mean_area", "mean_smoothness", "mean_compactness", "mean_concavity", "mean_concave_points", 
    "mean_fractal_dimension", "se_perimeter", "se_texture", "se_area"
]

# Fill missing values using mean, only for numeric columns
df_cln = df.copy()
df_cln[seleted_featues] = df[seleted_featues].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')  # Ensure numeric conversion
df_cln[seleted_featues] = df_cln[seleted_featues].fillna(df_cln[seleted_featues].mean())

# Extract features (X) and target variable (y)
X = df_cln[seleted_featues].values
y = np.where(df_cln["outcome"] == "N", 0, 1)  # Convert "N" to 0, "R" to 1
# Normalize features
X_mean, X_std = X.mean(axis=0), X.std(axis=0)
X_norm = (X - X_mean) / X_std
# Split into training and testing sets manually
trn_sze = int(0.8 * X_norm.shape[0])
X_trn, X_test = X_norm[:trn_sze], X_norm[trn_sze:]
y_train, y_tst = y[:trn_sze], y[trn_sze:]

# Sigmoid function
def sigmoid(z):
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))

# Logistic Regression model
def logistic_regression(X, y, alpha=0.01, iterations=1000):
    m, n = X.shape
    X_bias = np.c_[np.ones((m, 1)), X]  # Add bias term
    theta = np.zeros(n + 1)  # Initialize_parameters
    loss_history = []
    
    for _ in range(iterations):
        z = np.dot(X_bias, theta)
        h = sigmoid(z)
        loss = -np.mean(y * np.log(h) + (1 - y) * np.log(1 - h))
        gradient = np.dot(X_bias.T, (h - y)) / m
        theta -= alpha * gradient
        loss_history.append(loss)
    
    return theta, loss_history

# Forward selection function
def forward_selection(X, y):
    remain_featres = list(range(X.shape[1]))
    seleted_featues = []
    best_loss = float("inf")
    
    while remain_featres:
        feature_losses = []
        for feature in remain_featres:
            temp_features = seleted_featues + [feature]
            X_temp = X[:, temp_features]
            theta, loss_history = logistic_regression(X_temp, y)
            feature_losses.append((feature, loss_history[-1]))
        
        bst_feature, best_loss_current = min(feature_losses, key=lambda x: x[1])
        
        if best_loss_current < best_loss:
            seleted_featues.append(bst_feature)
            remain_featres.remove(bst_feature)
            best_loss = best_loss_current
        else:
            break
    
    return seleted_featues, best_loss

# Run forward selection
seleted_featues_idx, best_loss = forward_selection(X_trn, y_train)

##3c Comparision_two models
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Cancer_dataset1.csv")

# Selected Features
selcted_featues = [
    "mean_radius", "mean_texture", "mean_perimeter", "mean_area", "mean_smoothness", "mean_compactness", "mean_concavity", "mean_concave_points", 
    "mean_fractal_dimension", "se_perimeter", "se_texture", "se_area"
]

# Fill_missing values using mean, only num_colums
df_cln = df.copy()
df_cln[selcted_featues] = df[selcted_featues].apply(pd.to_numeric, errors='coerce')  # Ensure numeric conversion
df_cln[selcted_featues] = df_cln[selcted_featues].fillna(df_cln[selcted_featues].mean())

# Extract features (X) & target variable (y)
X = df_cln[selcted_featues].values
y = np.where(df_cln["outcome"] == "N", 0, 1)  # Convert "N" to 0, "R" to 1
# Normalize features
X_mean, X_std = X.mean(axis=0), X.std(axis=0)
X_norm = (X - X_mean) / X_std
# Split into training and testing sets manually
trn_sze = int(0.8 * X_norm.shape[0])
X_trn, X_test = X_norm[:trn_sze], X_norm[trn_sze:]
y_trn, y_test = y[:trn_sze], y[trn_sze:]

# Logistic Regression model
def sigmoid(z):
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))

def logistic_regression(X, y, alpha=0.01, iterations=1000):
    m, n = X.shape
    X_bias = np.c_[np.ones((m, 1)), X]  # Add bias term
    theta = np.zeros(n + 1)  # Initialize parameters
    loss_history = []
    
    for _ in range(iterations):
        z = np.dot(X_bias, theta)
        h = sigmoid(z)
        loss = -np.mean(y * np.log(h) + (1 - y) * np.log(1 - h))
        gradient = np.dot(X_bias.T, (h - y)) / m
        theta -= alpha * gradient
        loss_history.append(loss)
    
    return theta, loss_history

# Forward selection function
def forward_selection(X, y):
    remain_featres = list(range(X.shape[1]))
    selcted_featues = []
    best_loss = float("inf")
    
    while remain_featres:
        feature_losses = []
        for feature in remain_featres:
            temp_features = selcted_featues + [feature]
            X_temp = X[:, temp_features]
            theta, loss_history = logistic_regression(X_temp, y)
            feature_losses.append((feature, loss_history[-1]))
        
        best_feature, best_loss_current = min(feature_losses, key=lambda x: x[1])
        
        if best_loss_current < best_loss:
            selcted_featues.append(best_feature)
            remain_featres.remove(best_feature)
            best_loss = best_loss_current
        else:
            break
    
    return selcted_featues, best_loss

# Run forward selection
selcted_featues_idx, best_loss = forward_selection(X_trn, y_trn)
selected_feature_names = [selcted_featues[i] for i in selcted_featues_idx]
print("Selected Features:", selected_feature_names)

# Train model with all features (full model)
theta_full, loss_history_full = logistic_regression(X_trn, y_trn)

# Train model with selected features
X_trn_selected = X_trn[:, selcted_featues_idx]
X_test_selected = X_test[:, selcted_featues_idx]
theta_selected, loss_history_selected = logistic_regression(X_trn_selected, y_trn)

# Make Predictions
def predict(X, theta):
    X_bias = np.c_[np.ones((X.shape[0], 1)), X]
    return (sigmoid(np.dot(X_bias, theta)) >= 0.5).astype(int)

# Evaluate Full Model
y_pred_full = predict(X_test, theta_full)
TP_full = np.sum((y_pred_full == 1) & (y_test == 1))
TN_full = np.sum((y_pred_full == 0) & (y_test == 0))
FP_full = np.sum((y_pred_full == 1) & (y_test == 0))
FN_full = np.sum((y_pred_full == 0) & (y_test == 1))

# Evaluate Selected Features Model
y_pred_selected = predict(X_test_selected, theta_selected)
TP_selected = np.sum((y_pred_selected == 1) & (y_test == 1))
TN_selected = np.sum((y_pred_selected == 0) & (y_test == 0))
FP_selected = np.sum((y_pred_selected == 1) & (y_test == 0))
FN_selected = np.sum((y_pred_selected == 0) & (y_test == 1))

# Performance Metrics Calculation
def calculate_metrics(TP, TN, FP, FN):
    accuracy = (TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN) * 100
    precision = (TP / (TP + FP) * 100) if (TP + FP) != 0 else 0
    recall = (TP / (TP + FN) * 100) if (TP + FN) != 0 else 0
    f1_score = (2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall)) if (precision + recall) != 0 else 0
    return accuracy, precision, recall, f1_score

# Calculate metrics for both models
metris_full = calculate_metrics(TP_full, TN_full, FP_full, FN_full)
metris_selected = calculate_metrics(TP_selected, TN_selected, FP_selected, FN_selected)

#4a a)	Regularization_and_Feature_Scaling 

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Cancer_dataset1.csv")

# Convert'outcome' column from 'N-0' & 'R-1' 
df['outcome'] = df['outcome'].map({'N': 0, 'R': 1})
# Handle missing values
df.fillna(df.mean(), inplace=True)

# Define selected features and target
forwrd_bst_seleted_featues = [
    "mean_texture", "mean_area", "mean_smoothness", "mean_compactness", "mean_fractal_dimension", "se_perimeter", "se_texture"
]
X = df[forwrd_bst_seleted_featues].values
y = df["outcome"].values

# Train-test split (80% train, 20% test)
np.random.seed(42)
indices = np.random.permutation(len(X))
splt_idx = int(0.8 * len(X))
trn_idx, tst_idx = indices[:splt_idx], indices[splt_idx:]
X_trn, X_test = X[trn_idx], X[tst_idx]
y_trn, y_test = y[trn_idx], y[tst_idx]
# Oversampling only on the training data
cls_counts = np.bincount(y_trn)
max_class = np.argmax(cls_counts)
min_class = np.argmin(cls_counts)
diff = cls_counts[max_class] - cls_counts[min_class]
ovr_sampled_indices = np.random.choice(np.where(y_trn == min_class)[0], size=diff, replace=True)
X_trn = np.vstack((X_trn, X_trn[ovr_sampled_indices]))
y_trn = np.hstack((y_trn, y_trn[ovr_sampled_indices]))

# Normalization Function
def normalize(X):
    return (X - X.min(axis=0)) / (X.max(axis=0) - X.min(axis=0))
# Standardization Function
def standardize(X):
    return (X - X.mean(axis=0)) / X.std(axis=0)
# Regularization Implementations
def sigmoid(z):
    z = np.clip(z, -500, 500)
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-z))

def logistic_regression(X, y, lr=0.01, epochs=5000, lambda_reg=0, reg_type=None):
    m, n = X.shape
    theta = np.zeros(n)
    loss_histry = []  # List to store loss history
    for _ in range(epochs):
        z = np.dot(X, theta)
        h = sigmoid(z)
        gradient = np.dot(X.T, (h - y)) / m
        if reg_type == "lasso":
            gradient[1:] += (lambda_reg / m) * np.sign(theta[1:])
        elif reg_type == "ridge":
            gradient[1:] += (lambda_reg / m) * theta[1:]
        
        theta -= lr * gradient
        
        # Compute and store the loss
        loss = -np.mean(y * np.log(h + 1e-8) + (1 - y) * np.log(1 - h + 1e-8))  # Cross-entropy loss
        loss_histry.append(loss)
    
    return theta, loss_histry

# Compare Models
scaling_methods = {"Normalized": normalize(X_trn), "Standardized": standardize(X_trn)}
regularization_methods = ["No Regularization", "Lasso", "Ridge"]

results = []
loss_histories = []  # To store loss histories for plotting

for scale_type, X_scaled_train in scaling_methods.items():
    X_scaled_test = normalize(X_test) if scale_type == "Normalized" else standardize(X_test)
    X_trn_bias = np.c_[np.ones((X_scaled_train.shape[0], 1)), X_scaled_train]
    X_test_bias = np.c_[np.ones((X_scaled_test.shape[0], 1)), X_scaled_test]
    
    for reg_type in regularization_methods:
        lambda_reg = 0.1 if reg_type != "No Regularization" else 0
        theta, loss_histry = logistic_regression(X_trn_bias, y_trn, lr=0.01, epochs=5000, lambda_reg=lambda_reg, reg_type=None if reg_type == "No Regularization" else reg_type.lower())
        
        # Predictions on Test Data
        y_pred_test_prob = sigmoid(np.dot(X_test_bias, theta))
        y_pred_test = y_pred_test_prob >= 0.5
        
        # Compute Confusion Matrix Metrics
        TP = np.sum((y_pred_test == 1) & (y_test == 1))
        TN = np.sum((y_pred_test == 0) & (y_test == 0))
        FP = np.sum((y_pred_test == 1) & (y_test == 0))
        FN = np.sum((y_pred_test == 0) & (y_test == 1))
        
        confusion_matrix = np.array([[TN, FP], [FN, TP]])
        print(f"Confusion Matrix for {scale_type} - {reg_type} on Test Data:\n {confusion_matrix}\n")

        accuracy = ((TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN)) * 100
        precision = (TP / (TP + FP) * 100) if (TP + FP) != 0 else 0 
        recall = (TP / (TP + FN) * 100) if (TP + FN) != 0 else 0
        f1_score = (2 * precision * recall) / (precision + recall) if (precision + recall) != 0 else 0

        results.append({
            "Scaling": scale_type,
            "Regularization": reg_type,
            "Accuracy": accuracy,
            "Precision": precision,
            "Recall": recall,
            "F1 Score": f1_score
        })
        
        # Store the loss history for plotting
        loss_histories.append((scale_type, reg_type, loss_histry))

# Convert results to DataFrame
results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)

# Plot Metrics Comparison
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(20, 5))
metrics = ["Accuracy", "Precision", "Recall", "F1 Score"]
titles = ["Accuracy", "Precision", "Recall", "F1 Score"]

for i, metric in enumerate(metrics):
    sns.barplot(x="Regularization", y=metric, hue="Scaling", data=results_df, ax=ax[i])
    ax[i].set_title(titles[i])
    ax[i].set_xlabel("")
    ax[i].set_ylabel(metric)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Print results
print(results_df)

# Plot Loss Convergence
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
for scale_type, reg_type, loss_histry in loss_histories:
    ax.plot(loss_histry, label=f"{scale_type} - {reg_type}")
ax.set_xlabel("Iterations")
ax.set_ylabel("Loss")
ax.set_title("Loss Convergence for Different Models")
ax.legend(title="Scaling and Regularization", bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# 4b i)CostFunction_usng MSE

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

# Load dataset
df = pd.read_csv("Cancer_dataset1.csv")
# Convert 'outcome' column from 'N' & 'R' to 0 & 1
df['outcome'] = df['outcome'].map({'N': 0, 'R': 1})

# Convert non-numeric columns to numeric (if any)
non_numeric_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns
for col in non_numeric_cols:
    if col != "outcome":
        df[col] = pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors='coerce')
# Handle_missing_values
df.fillna(df.mean(), inplace=True)

# Define features & target
features = [
    "mean_texture", "mean_area", "mean_smoothness", "mean_compactness", "mean_fractal_dimension", "se_perimeter", "se_texture"
]
X = df[features].values  # Feture_matrix
y = df["outcome"].values  # Taget_variable

# Normalize_features
X_mean, X_std = X.mean(axis=0), X.std(axis=0)
X_norm = (X - X_mean) / X_std  # Standardization

# Train-test split
np.random.seed(42)
indices = np.random.permutation(len(X_norm))
splt_idx = int(0.8 * len(X_norm))
train_idx, test_idx = indices[:splt_idx], indices[splt_idx:]
X_trn, X_test = X_norm[train_idx], X_norm[test_idx]
y_train, y_test = y[train_idx], y[test_idx]

# Add bias term
X_trn_bias = np.c_[np.ones((X_trn.shape[0], 1)), X_trn]
X_test_bias = np.c_[np.ones((X_test.shape[0], 1)), X_test]

# Sigmoid function
def sigmoid(z):
    return 1 / (1 + np.exp(-np.clip(z, -250, 250)))  # Avoid overflow

# Logistic Regression with MSE Loss and L2 Regularization
def logistic_regression(X, y, lr=0.01, epochs=5000, lambda_reg=0.1):
    m, n = X.shape
    theta = np.zeros(n)
    loss_history = []

    for _ in range(epochs):
        z = np.dot(X, theta)
        h = sigmoid(z)

        # Compute MSE Loss_with_L2_Regularization
        mse_loss = (1 / (2 * m)) * np.sum((h - y) ** 2) + (lambda_reg / (2 * m)) * np.sum(theta[1:] ** 2)
        loss_history.append(mse_loss)

        # Compute Gradient
        gradient = (np.dot(X.T, (h - y)) / m) + (lambda_reg / m) * np.r_[0, theta[1:]]
        theta -= lr * gradient  # Update weights

    return theta, loss_history

# Train the model with MSE Loss
theta, loss_history = logistic_regression(X_trn_bias, y_train, lr=0.01, epochs=5000, lambda_reg=0.1)

# Compute MSE for Train and Test Data
def compute_mse(X, y, theta):
    predictions = sigmoid(np.dot(X, theta))
    return np.mean((predictions - y) ** 2)
mse_trn = compute_mse(X_trn_bias, y_train, theta)
mse_tst = compute_mse(X_test_bias, y_test, theta)

print(f"\nMSE for Train Predictions: {mse_trn:.6f}")
print(f"MSE for Test Predictions: {mse_tst:.6f}")

# Predictions using fixed threshold of 0.5
def predict(X, theta, threshold=0.5):
    return (sigmoid(np.dot(X, theta)) >= threshold).astype(int)

y_pred_test = predict(X_test_bias, theta, threshold=0.5)
# Compute Confusion Matrix
TP = np.sum((y_pred_test == 1) & (y_test == 1))
TN = np.sum((y_pred_test == 0) & (y_test == 0))
FP = np.sum((y_pred_test == 1) & (y_test == 0))
FN = np.sum((y_pred_test == 0) & (y_test == 1))

conf_matrix = np.array([[TN, FP], [FN, TP]])

# Print Confusion Matrix
print("\nConfusion Matrix:")
print(f"                Predicted No   Predicted Yes")
print(f"Actual No     |    {TN}         {FP}  |  (TN  FP)")
print(f"Actual Yes    |    {FN}         {TP}  |  (FN  TP)")

# Compute Performance Metrics
accuracy = (TP + TN) / (TP + TN + FP + FN)
precision = TP / (TP + FP + 1e-10)
recall = TP / (TP + FN + 1e-10)
f1_score = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall + 1e-10)

# Print Performance Metrics
print(f"Accuracy: {accuracy * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Precision: {precision * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"Recall: {recall * 100:.2f}%")
print(f"F1 Score: {f1_score * 100:.2f}%")

# Plot Loss Curve
plt.plot(loss_history)
plt.xlabel("Iterations")
plt.ylabel("MSE Loss")
plt.title("Logistic Regression Loss (MSE)")
plt.show()

# Plot Confusion Matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(5, 4))
sns.heatmap(conf_matrix, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="Blues", 
            xticklabels=["No Recurrence", "Recurrence"], 
            yticklabels=["No Recurrence", "Recurrence"])
plt.xlabel("Predicted Label")
plt.ylabel("True Label")
plt.title("Confusion Matrix for Logistic Regression")
plt.show()

#4b #ii)Compare the performance of both the models (4.b.i and 4.a.)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

# Initial Results
data = {
    'Scaling': ['Normlized__', 'Normlized__', 'Normlized__',
                'Standardized', 'Standardized', 'Standardized',
                'Other'],
    'Regularization': ['No Regularization', 'Lasso', 'Ridge',
                       'No Regularization', 'Lasso', 'Ridge',
                       'Cost Function Confusion'],
    'Accuracy': [67.5, 65.0, 67.5, 50.0, 50.0, 50.0, 82.5],
    'Precision': [18.18, 16.67, 18.18, 15.0, 15.0, 15.0, 0.0],
    'Recall': [33.33, 33.33, 33.33, 50.0, 50.0, 50.0, 0.0],
    'F1 Score': [23.53, 22.22, 23.53, 23.08, 23.08, 23.08, 0.0]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Metrics to plot
metric_s = ['Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1 Score']
bar_width = 0.2
x = np.arange(len(metric_s))
# Filter by category
normlized__ = df[df['Scaling'] == 'Normlized__']
standardized = df[df['Scaling'] == 'Standardized']
other = df[df['Scaling'] == 'Other']

# Plot
fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6), sharey=True)
fig.suptitle('Comparison of Feature Scaling, Regularization & Cost Function Confusion Matrix', fontsize=15)
# --- Subplot 1: Normlized__ + Cost Function
for idx, reg in enumerate(normlized__['Regularization']):
    values = normlized__.iloc[idx][metric_s].values
    axs[0].bar(x + idx * bar_width, values, width=bar_width, label=reg)

# Add Cost Function Confusion Metrics to Normlized__ chart
cst_metris = other.iloc[0][metric_s].values
axs[0].bar(x + 3 * bar_width, cst_metris, width=bar_width, label='Cost Confusion', color='gray')

axs[0].set_title('Normlized__ + Cost Function')
axs[0].set_xticks(x + 1.5 * bar_width)
axs[0].set_xticklabels(metric_s)
axs[0].legend()
axs[0].set_ylabel('Metric Value (%)')
axs[0].set_ylim(0, 100)

# --- Subplot 2: Standardized + Cost Function
for idx, reg in enumerate(standardized['Regularization']):
    values = standardized.iloc[idx][metric_s].values
    axs[1].bar(x + idx * bar_width, values, width=bar_width, label=reg)

axs[1].bar(x + 3 * bar_width, cst_metris, width=bar_width, label='Cost Confusion', color='gray')

axs[1].set_title('Standardized + Cost Function')
axs[1].set_xticks(x + 1.5 * bar_width)
axs[1].set_xticklabels(metric_s)
axs[1].legend()

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Cost function and confusion matrix values
mse_train = 0.172773
mse_test = 0.145555

# Plotting MSE and final confusion matrix
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))

# MSE Bar
plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
plt.bar(['Train MSE', 'Test MSE'], [mse_train, mse_test], color=['skyblue', 'salmon'])
plt.title('Cost Function (MSE)')
plt.ylabel('Mean Squared Error')

# Final Confusion Matrix Performance
final_conf = {'Accuracy': 82.5, 'Precision': 0.0, 'Recall': 0.0, 'F1 Score': 0.0}

plt.bar(final_conf.keys(), final_conf.values(), color='orange')
plt.title('Final Confusion Matrix Metrics')

plt.ylabel('Metric Value (%)')
